Instructions

BTracT Laboratory Labels

How it works

Follow these steps to print barcode labels for the test tubes in the laboratory.

Step 1: Download data

1. Go to, btract labels (login)

2. Browse to the respective page

  • Crosses
  • Seeds germinating after 8 weeks
  • PLantlets/ Subcultures

3. Downlod data

To download specific barcodes, select their respective rows in the given table. By not selecting any row in the data table, all records barcodes will be available for download


Step 2: Print barcode labels


1. Open the respective label format (double click to open)

Crosses


2. Database connection


Databases icon >> Create database connection

Connect label to data


3. Select downloaded data


  • Click the back button as highlighted



  • Browse where the data is located and open it

Browse to data file location


  • Ensure all the fields are selected as shown. Click NEXT to proceed


  • Keep the default and click Finish


  • Finally, print the labels. Click on the print icon, as highlighted


  • Click Print to print labels. Or preview before printing
